        <div1 type="body">
            


<p><placeName>Mine a Burton</placeName> <date when="1811-06-04">June 4</date></p>
<p><persName>Mr James Bryan</persName></p>

<p><persName>Mr Ayres</persName> has on board his Waggon Barres lead in all
pounds. 750 of which is of your lead and 212 from my furnace which
I have given him to make out the load <persName>Mr Bates</persName> has this day Visited
<persName>Mr Westover</persName> to obtain an order for lead at <placeName><persName>Mr Elliott</persName>s</placeName>&#8212;<persName>P W Love</persName>
could not load the Cart&#8212;</p>

<p><persName>Moses Austin</persName>    [Rubric]</p>

<p>Reced from <persName>Moses Austin</persName> Nineteen-Barrs lead which I promes</p>

<p>to&#8212;delivere <persName>Mr Bryan</persName> <placeName>Saint Genevieve</placeName> with out, delay&#8212;As Witness
my hand&#8212;this <date when="1811-06-04">4 day <hi rend="italic">June 1811</hi></date></p>

<p><persName>Francis (his x mark) Ayres</persName></p>
<p>Attest   <persName>G. W. <hi rend="italic">Treat</hi></persName></p>


        </div1>
